People subconsciously assume that caves automatically contain themselves inside the map borders, that they do not cross freely deep into foreign territory. In a way the chthonic depths thus show nation borders as "arbitrary" in a sense of underground subversion, rhizomasomething.

My grandpa knew the son of a CIA agent who was stalked by the secret police and managed to escape Soviet Bulgaria through taking a cave system leading into Greece, below the border, not well mapped out. I think lots of people are aware of similar "shortcuts". Good to keep in mind
